'''FaceGlat''' ({{lang-he|פייסגלאט}}) is a [[social networking]] service by Yaakov Swisa. The website caters to [[Haredi Judaism|Haredi Jew]]s. The website separates users by sex and screens comments and advertisements to prevent indecency. The website currently is available in English and Hebrew. Swisa said that he plans to add French and Russian versions.<ref>Ravitz, Jessica. "[http://religion.blogs.cnn.com/2011/09/12/faceglat-can-social-media-be-made-kosher/?hpt=hp_t2 FaceGlat: Can social media be made kosher?]." ''[[CNN]]''. September 12, 2011. Retrieved on September 12, 2011.</ref> Swisa said that he considered having a system where men and women who are members of the same family would be allowed to friend each other, but decided against it because he believed it would result in impersonations and individuals using false identities.<ref>Nahshoni, Kobi. "[http://www.ynetnews.com/articles/0,7340,L-4098443,00.html New: 'Segregated Facebook' for haredim]." ''[[Ynet]]''. July 24, 2011. Retrieved on September 12, 2011.</ref>

