{{Infobox person | image = Flickr - Israel Defense Forces - IDF Coordination with American Doctor.jpg | image_size = 250 | name = Jennifer Ashton | caption = Ashton in [[2010 Haiti earthquake|Haiti after the earthquake, 2010]] | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1969|4|23|mf=y}} | birth_place = [[George Air Force Base]], [[California]], U.S. | death_date = | death_place = | occupation = Ob-Gyn | salary = | networth = | spouse = Dr. Robert C. Ashton, Jr. (divorced) | children = Alex, Chloë | footnotes = }}
'''Jennifer Lee Ashton''' (born April 23, 1969) is a [[physician]], author, and [[television]] [[correspondent]]. She is chief health and medical editor and chief [[medical journalism|medical correspondent]] for ''[[ABC News]]'' and ''[[Good Morning America]]'', chief [[women's health]] correspondent for ''[[The Dr. Oz Show]]'', and a columnist for ''[[Cosmopolitan Magazine]]''. She is also a frequent [[guest speaker]] and [[Discussion moderator|moderator]] for events raising awareness of women's health issues.{{citation needed|date=July 2018}}
She is authorized by the [[United States national team|Team USA]] [[preferred provider organization|medical network]] to care for female U.S. [[Olympic Games|Olympian]]s.{{citation needed|date=July 2018}}
== Early life and education == Ashton was born in [[California]] to Oscar Garfein, a New York City [[cardiologist]], and Dorothy Garfein, a [[registered nurse]]. Her brother, Evan Garfein, is chief of [[plastic|plastic surgery]] and [[reconstructive surgery]] at [[Montefiore Medical Center|Montefiore Hospital]] in [[New York City]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.montefiore.org/body.cfm?id=1735&action=detail&ref=3252|title=|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=|access-date=}}</ref>
She attended [[Horace Mann School]] in [[Riverdale, Bronx|Riverdale]], New York City,<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.horacemann.org/mobile.cfm?p=1080&newsid=221 |title = Women’s Issues Club Dinner on Body Image Features Alumni Panelists |website = Horace Mann School |accessdate = January 16, 2014}}</ref> where she studied [[French language|French]] and [[English studies|English]].
In 1991, she graduated from [[Columbia College, Columbia University]], with a [[bachelor's degree]] in [[art history]].<ref name="cbsjoin">{{cite web|url=http://www.cbsnews.com/news/dr-jennifer-ashton-new-med-correspondent/|title=Dr. Jennifer Ashton: New Med Correspondent|date=April 1, 2009|website=CBS News|accessdate=January 16, 2014}}</ref><ref name=mediabistro>{{cite web |url = http://www.mediabistro.com/tvnewser/cbs-the-early-show-hires-new-doc_b29027 |title = CBS’ The Early Show Hires New Doc |last = Ariens |first = Chris|date = March 31, 2009 |website = Mediabistro |accessdate = January 16, 2014}}</ref>
She received her [[doctor of medicine|medical degree]] from [[Columbia College of Physicians and Surgeons]] in 2000.<ref name=cbsjoin /><ref name=thedoctors>{{cite web |url = http://www.thedoctorstv.com/doctors/main?name=Jennifer+Ashton |title = Dr. Jennifer Asthon|website = The Doctors|accessdate = January 16, 2014}}</ref>
In 2016, she received her [[master's degree]] in [[dietetics|nutrition]] from Columbia University.<ref name=thedoctors /><ref>{{cite web |url = http://jenniferashtonmd.com/dr-ashton-off-duty/why-i-decided-to-go-back-to-school-/2013/12/03/ |title = Why I decided to go back to school???!! |last = Jennifer |first = Asthon |date = December 3, 2013|website = Jennifer Ashton MD |accessdate =January 16, 2014}}</ref>
==Career== A [[board certification|board-certified]] [[obstetrician]] and [[gynecologist]],<ref name=bio>{{cite web |url = http://jenniferashtonmd.com/dr-ashtons-bio/ |title = Dr. Ashton's Bio |website = Jennifer Ashton MD |publisher=The Brooks Group|accessdate =January 16, 2014}}</ref> Ashton completed her [[medical residency|residency]] at [[St. Luke's–Roosevelt Hospital Center]] in New York.<ref name=cbsjoin /><ref name=mediabistro />
She has practiced as an [[attending physician]] at [[Englewood Hospital and Medical Center]], an affiliate of [[Mount Sinai Medical Center]] in [[Englewood, New Jersey|Englewood]], New Jersey, and is currently in private practice.<ref name=wysk >{{cite web |url = http://www.womenyoushouldknow.net/all-about-the-thyroid-with-dr-jennifer-ashton/ |title = All About The Thyroid With Dr. Jennifer Ashton |date = February 12, 2012|website = Women You Should Know |accessdate =January 16, 2014}}</ref>
Ashton has authored numerous magazine articles and contributed to a health blog for ''[[The Record (Bergen County)|The Record]]'' of [[Bergen County, New Jersey|Bergen, New Jersey]].{{citation needed|date=July 2018}} In addition, she has written three books: ''The Body Scoop for Girls'' (2009), which educates teenage girls on the topic of [[puberty]]; ''Your Body Beautiful'' (2012), which addresses health and [[Wellness (alternative medicine)|wellness]] issues in [[middle age|middle-aged]] women; and ''Eat This When You're Expecting, Not That'' (2016), in which she outlines a diet designed specifically for [[pregnancy|pregnant]] women.{{citation needed|date=July 2018}}
Ashton launched her television career in 2006 as the first female medical contributor to the [[Fox News Channel]].<ref name=cbsjoin /><ref name=mediabistro /><ref name=dhs>{{cite web|url=http://www.dhsliterary.com/authors/ashton.aspx |title=Jennifer Ashton |website=David Hale Smith Literary |accessdate=January 16, 2014 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141214163611/http://www.dhsliterary.com/authors/ashton.aspx |archivedate=December 14, 2014 |df= }}</ref> She appeared on [[The Learning Channel]]'s ''[[A Baby Story]]'', on [[PBS]], and on [[Oprah & Friends]] [[XM radio]]'s ''The Dr. Oz Show''.<ref name=dhs /><ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.englewoodhospital.com/about_news_press_09_15.asp |title = Dr. Jennifer Ashton Named CBS Broadcast News Correspondent |date = April 15, 2009 |website = Englewood Hospital and Medical Center |accessdate = January 16, 2014}}</ref>
She joined [[CBS News]] as a medical correspondent in 2009,<ref name=cbsjoin /><ref name=mediabistro /> contributing to all CBS media platforms, with regular appearances on ''[[The CBS Evening News with Katie Couric]]'' and ''[[The Early Show]]''. She remains a featured expert commentator on [[WCBS (AM)|WCBS Radio]] and its national affiliates.{{citation needed|date=July 2018}}
Ashton co-hosted the shortlived ABC television series ''[[The Revolution (TV series)|The Revolution]]'', canceled in April 2012 due to poor viewership.<ref name=bio /><ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.broadwayworld.com/bwwtv/article/Jennifer-Ashton-Tiffanie-Davis-Henry-Join-ABC-Daytimes-THE-REVOLUTION-20111031 |title = Jennifer Ashton, Tiffanie Davis Henry Join ABC Daytime's The Revolution | last = |first = |date = October 31, 2011 |website = broadwayworld.com |publisher = Wisdom Digital Media |accessdate = January 16, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url = https://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/tv-column/post/abc-cancels-the-revolution-hangs-on-to-general-hospital/2012/04/11/gIQA87sHBT_blog.html |title = ABC cancels 'The Revolution,' hangs on to 'General Hospital' |last = de Moraes|first = Lisa |date = April 11, 2012 |website = Washington Post |accessdate = January 16, 2014}}</ref>
She joined the ABC News medical unit as senior medical contributor in 2012, making regular appearances on ''Good Morning America'' and ''[[ABC World News Tonight]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url = http://abcnews.go.com/blogs/headlines/2012/10/dr-jennifer-ashton-joins-abc-news/ |title = Dr. Jennifer Ashton Joins ABC News |date = October 22, 2012 |website = ABC News |publisher = |accessdate = January 16, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.abcmedianet.com/web/bios/display_bios.aspx?bio_type=news_correspondents&bio_id=409 |title=Dr. Jennifer Ashton |website=ABC MediaNet |accessdate=January 16, 2014 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140829151618/http://www.abcmedianet.com/web/bios/display_bios.aspx?bio_type=news_correspondents&bio_id=409 |archivedate=August 29, 2014 |df= }}</ref>
In 2013 she became an [[on-air personality]] for the daytime talk show ''[[The Doctors (2008 TV series)|The Doctors]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.bergen.com/people/New_Gig_Englewoods_Dr_Jennifer_Ashton_joins_CBS_Televisions_The_Doctors.html |title = New Gig: Englewood's Dr. Jennifer Ashton joins "The Doctors" |date = October 15, 2013 |website = bergen.com |accessdate = January 16, 2014}}</ref>
==Personal life== In January 2017, Ashton divorced Robert Ashton Jr., a [[thoracic surgeon|thoracic]] and [[cardiac surgeon]] with whom she had two children, Alex and Chloe. On February 11, two weeks after the divorce was finalized, Robert, 52, committed [[suicide]] by jumping off the [[George Washington Bridge]].<ref>{{cite web|author-last=DeMarco|author-first=Jerry|title=TV Medical Personality's Ex Jumps To Death From GWB|url=http://fortlee.dailyvoice.com/police-fire/tv-medical-personalitys-ex-jumps-to-death-from-gwb/699612/|website=Fort Lee Daily Voice|publisher=Cantata Media|accessdate=18 July 2018|date=12 February 2017|deadurl=no|df=}}</ref> On June 6, 2018, after news of [[Kate Spade]]’s suicide broke, Ashton went public about her ex-husband’s death during an interview with colleague [[George Stephanapoulos]] on ''[[Good Morning America]]''.
Ashton has revealed that she learned [[Transcendental Meditation technique|Transcendental Meditation]] through the [[David Lynch Foundation]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Healthy Hollywood: Jennifer Ashton|url=http://www.skinnymom.com/2014/12/07/healthy-hollywood-jennifer-ashton/|website=Skinny Mom|accessdate=15 December 2014|date=7 December 2014|quote=I felt that my body was in shape, but I needed to take care of my mind and spirit better. TM is easy, and involves just 20 min, twice a day. It is a great way to prevent or deal with stress. That’s my mental wellness ritual now|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141215232227/http://www.skinnymom.com/2014/12/07/healthy-hollywood-jennifer-ashton/|archivedate=15 December 2014|df=}}</ref>
==Bibliography== * ''The Body Scoop for Girls: A Straight-Talk Guide to a Healthy, Beautiful You'', by Jennifer Ashton M.D., Ob-Gyn with Christine Larson, 2009, {{ISBN|1-5833-3458-0}}. * ''Your Body Beautiful: Clockstopping Secrets to Staying Healthy, Strong, and Sexy in Your 30s, 40s, and Beyond'', by Jennifer Ashton M.D., Ob-Gyn with Christine Rojo, 2012, {{ISBN|1-5833-3458-0}}. * Eat This When You're Expecting, Not That: Your Complete Guide to the Very Best Foods For Every Stage of Pregnancy, by America's leading OB/GYN Jennifer Ashton, MD and David Zinczenko, 2016.
==Awards and honors== In 2007, Ashton was recognized as a Woman of Achievement by the Girl Scouts of Northern New Jersey.<ref name=wysk /> In 2008, she received the Hope for The Future Award from [http://www.octoberwoman.org The Octoberwoman Foundation for Breast Cancer Awareness].<ref name=wysk />
==Organizations== Ashton is a member of the North American Society for Pediatric and Adolescent Gynecology and a Fellow of the American College of Obstetricians and Gynecologists.<ref>{{cite book | title=Your Body Beautiful: Clockstopping Secrets to Staying Healthy, Strong, and Sexy in Your 30s, 40s, and Beyond |last1=Ashton MD |first1=Jennifer |last2=Rojo |first2=Christine |year=2012 |publisher=Penguin Books Ltd. |isbn=1583334580 }}</ref> She serves on the Board of Trustees of The Arnold P. Gold Foundation for Humanism in Medicine and of The Community Chest.{{Citation needed|date=January 2014}}
