{{refimprove|date=August 2016}} {{Universal Sufism}} All [[Sufi]] orders have their own ''[[Silsila]]'' or Chain of Transmission. The representation of the Chain of Transmission is called the ''Shajara'' ("Tree"). Below is that of the [[Sufi Order Ināyati]] up to [[Inayat Khan]]. The Shajara which appears here is that of [[Inayat Khan]]'s primary spiritual lineage, the [[Chishti]] Order, although he was also initiated into the [[Suhrawardiyya|Suhrawardi]], [[Naqshbandi]] and [[Qadiri]] Sufi orders.
Silsilas always begin with God, so the ''Shajara'' will begin with the name [[Allah]], but in the [[Western Sufist]] context this should not be confined to the concept of Allah within Islam, but should be seen as [[Spirit of Guidance|Universal Intelligence]]. The Sufi Order International ''shajra'' is in fact derived until Inayat Khan, from the Chishti-Nizami line of traditional Chishti Sufism but branches off later, on its own thereafter.
==The original Shajrah== * Knowledge from [[Allah]] (via) Jibrail (Archangel Gabriel) * [[Muhammad]] * Syedna [[Ali ibn Abi Talib]] * Khwaja [[Hasan Basri]] * Khwaja Abd al-Wahid bin Zayd * Khwaja Fuzayl bin Iyaz * Khwaja Ibrahim Adham * Khwaja Saadudin Huzayfa al Mar’ishi * Khwaja Aminuddin Hubayra al Basri * Khwaja Mumshad ‘Ulu Dinwari (Alwi) * Khwaja [[Abu Ishaq Shami]] Chishti (who is credited with starting the Chishti order proper in Chisht, Afghanistan) * Khwaja Abu Ahmad Abdal Chishti * Khwaja Abu Muhammad Chishti * Khwaja Qutbuddin Mawdud Chishti * Khwaja Hajji Sharif Zindani * Khwaja Usman Haruni * Khwaja [[Moinuddin Chishti|Moinuddin Hasan Sanjari-Ajmeri]] * Khwaja [[Qutbuddin Bakhtiar Kaki|Qutbuddin Mas’ud Bakhtiyar Kaki]] * Khwaja Fariduddin Masu'ud Ganj-i Shakar Ajhodani (Pakpattan sharif, Pakistan) * Khwaja [[Nizamuddin Auliya|Nizamuddin Mahbub Illahi Badauni]](The Chishti-Nizami branch of Chishti Sufism starts with him) * Khwaja [[Nasiruddin Chiragh Dehlavi]] * Shaykh al-Masha’ikh Kamaluddin ‘Allama Bande Nawaz * Shaykh al-Masha’ikh [[Munabbih ibn Kamil|Sirajuddin]] * Shaykh al-Masha'ikh ´Ilmuddin * Shaykh al-Masha’ikh Mahmud Rajan * Shaykh al-Masha’ikh Jamaluddin Jumman * Shaykh al-Masha’ikh Hasan Muhammad * Shaykh al-Masha’ikh Muhammad A’zam * Shaykh al-Masha’ikh Yahya Madani * Shaykh al-Masha’ikh Shah Kalim Ullah Jahanabadi * Shaykh al-Masha’ikh Nizamuddin Awrangabadi * Shaykh al-Masha’ikh Maulana Fakhruddin Fakhre Jahan * Shaykh al-Masha’ikh Ghulam Qutbuddin * Shaykh al-Masha’ikh Nasiruddin Mahmud Kali Shah * Shaykh al-Masha’ikh Muhammad Hasan Jili Kalimi * Shaykh al-Masha’ikh Abu Hashim Madani * Pir Inayat Khan etc. thereafter <ref>[http://www.centrum-universel.com/silsilae.htm Silsila / Shajara - The Chain of Spiritual Transmission<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>
