{{Taoism}}
A '''Taoist temple''' ({{cjkv|t=觀|s=观|p=guān}}, also {{lang|zh|道观}} ''dàoguān'', literally "[place] where the [[Tao]] is observed/cultivated") is a place of worship in [[Taoism]].

Structure and function can vary according to the [[Taoist schools|Taoist school]] the temple belongs to. For example, ''guān'' of the [[Quanzhen School]] are [[monastery|monasteries]] where celibate [[Taoist priest]]s live.

The title ''gōng'' ({{cjkv|t=宫}}) "palace" is often used for large temples built with imperial or governmental patronage.

[[File:Interior of the Leong San See temple, Singapore.jpg|thumb|Interior of the [[Leong San See temple]], Singapore]]

