{{About|the Hindu tradition|the Kannada language movie|Yajamana (movie)}} [[File:Arnuna donated Animals to Brahmins.jpg|thumb|250px| A priest and a yajamana]] In the Hindu tradition, a '''''yajamana''''' is the ritual patron, on whose behalf a religious ritual or a ''[[yajna]]'' is performed by a priest, generally a [[Brahmin]].<ref>Mantra, SUNY Series in Religious Studies, Harvey P. Alper, SUNY Press, 1989 p. 51</ref><ref>Society and Religion: From Rugveda to Puranas, Jayant Gadkari, Popular Prakashan, 1996 p. 27</ref> The term ''Yajamana'', also corrupted to ''[[Eshmanan]]'' was a term to address [[Nair|Nayar]] and [[Kshatriya]] feudal landlords in [[Kerala]]
